Biography

Michael Manley ON OCC is Notable.

Michael Manley ON OCC has African ancestry.

Michael Manley ON OCC was born in Jamaica.

Michael Manley was born in Saint Andrew Parish on 10 December 1924. He was the son of Norman Manley and Edna Swithenbank.

He was elected to the Parliament of Jamaica in 1962, following his father - who had been elected Chief Minister of Jamaica in 1955 - into politics. In 1972, he succeeded Hugh Shearer as Prime Minister and began to promote a republican approach to Jamaican politics.

Michael died in Kingston on 6 March 1997, and was buried in National Heroes Park, Kingston.[1]
